main event: An officer sighted a star-like object traveling from the NW to the SE in Natrona, Pennsylvania.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on December 30, 1968, at 7:00 PM,The observer described the object as luminous and oval-shaped, approximately 50 feet in diameter,The object hovered about 200 feet above the ground and had a bright light around its perimeter,The object remained in view for about 5 minutes before moving out of sight,The report indicates that there were no confirmed photographs of the event.
